You need to update your Firestore security rules to allow writing to the prescriptions collection. Here are a few options:

**Option 1: Allow all users to write to prescriptions (for testing)**
```javascript
rules_version = '2';

service cloud.firestore {
 match /databases/{database}/documents {
 match /prescriptions/{document} {
 allow read, write: if true;
 }
 match /{document=**} {
 allow read, write: if false;
 }
 }
}
```

**Option 2: Allow only authenticated users (recommended)**
```javascript
rules_version = '2';

service cloud.firestore {
 match /databases/{database}/documents {
 match /prescriptions/{document} {
 allow read, write: if request.auth != null;
 }
 match /{document=**} {
 allow read, write: if false;
 }
 }
}
```

**Option 3: Allow users to only write their own prescriptions (most secure)**
```javascript
rules_version = '2';

service cloud.firestore {
 match /databases/{database}/documents {
 match /prescriptions/{document} {
 allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == resource.data.userId;
 allow create: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.userId;
 }
 match /{document=**} {
 allow read, write: if false;
 }
 }
}
```

If you choose Option 3, you'll also need to add the user ID to your saved prescription data:

```kotlin:app/src/main/java/com/aritradas/medai/data/repository/PrescriptionRepositoryImpl.kt
override suspend fun savePrescription(prescription: SavedPrescription): Resource<String> {
 return withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {
 try {
 val user = FirebaseAuth.getInstance().currentUser
 if (user == null) {
 return@withContext Resource.Error("User not authenticated")
 }

 val prescriptionData = hashMapOf(
 "summary" to prescription.summary,
 "savedAt" to prescription.savedAt,
 "title" to prescription.title,
 "userId" to user.uid
 )

 val documentRef = firestore.collection("prescriptions")
 .add(prescriptionData)
 .await()

 Resource.Success(documentRef.id)
 } catch (e: Exception) {
 Resource.Error("Failed to save prescription: ${e.message}")
 }
 }
}
```

